Advantages
Provides automatic recovery from server failures.
Minimizes application downtime and service interruptions.
Improves application availability and reliability.
Automatically scales infrastructure during high traffic periods.
Reduces operational costs by using resources only when required.
Eliminates continuous manual infrastructure monitoring.
Improves application performance through efficient load balancing.
Supports business continuity during unexpected failures.
Offers better customer experience with consistent service availability.
Easily scalable for organizations of different sizes.
Limitations
Requires knowledge of AWS services and cloud architecture.
Incorrect Auto Scaling policies may increase operational costs.
AWS services incur usage-based charges.
Monitoring multiple cloud services can become complex.
Internet connectivity is required to access cloud infrastructure.
Security configurations must be properly managed to prevent vulnerabilities.
